SIMPLE: paraboloid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paraboloid
<hw>Pa*rab"o*loid</hw> <pr>(-loid)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Parabola</ets> + <ets>-oid</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>parabolo⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>The solid
generated by the rotation of a parabola about its axis; any surface of
the second order whose sections by planes parallel to a given line are
parabolas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term <xex>paraboloid</xex> has sometimes been
applied also to the parabolas of the higher orders.</note>
<rj><au>Hutton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paraboloidal</ent>⟦br⟧
